I even had time to watch football & go for a walk with my husband before he went to work. I missed my oldest two, but I enjoyed every minute of this day. 

Sunday’s are for soaking up every second!!

social_posts.post_text: I was supposed to be a billionaire cosmetologist, living in a mansion, with one kid, traveling the world, eating chicken tenders in the Bahamas, listening to music with my husband and French bulldog. 🤣

Proverbs 31:17 She girdeth her loins with strength, and strengtheneth her arms.
 
Showing her readiness to every good work; and with what cheerfulness, spirit, and resolution…

As wives and mothers we work full time. Some at home and others have a job, but we’re all working from the time our eyes open until they close. I rarely sit down. We take care of the home and our children. We don’t have to worry a whole lot about working out for hours every day since we get a lot of exercise raising children and caring for our homes. We don’t focus too much on ourselves. 

When my oldest was little I’d go out looking like a big mess. I was a big mess. I didn’t do anything for myself. I rarely got to wash my hair. Now people may assume that I’m vein or conceited. I’m not. I know that my worth has already been determined by my maker and a price was paid for me. I am more precious than rubies. Fearfully and wonderfully made. 

I wear makeup because my abusive ex wouldn’t allow me too, and my husband now tells me I’m perfect either way- but spoils me with lots of makeup. I love to be creative. My face is a canvas. I style my hair, wear stylish clothing & do my nails while I listen to a podcast, book or watch a movie. This is the perfect downtime for me as a Mom, because if I’m not focused on a task for myself, I’m cleaning, cooking, or checking off a long to do list. This calms my mind. 

I go to the gym to focus on my health and fitness. I grew up eating very unhealthy foods, in a family full of smokers-I lost my Momma young to lung cancer, we never drank water or went on walks. I was never taught health or fitness, and I want to be around and as healthy as long as I can. I love to challenge myself at the gym. This doesn’t mean I don’t enjoy sweet tea, snacks or huge cheeseburgers. Girl gotta eat! 

You can’t pour from an empty cup. Do what makes you happy! I choose to strengthen my mind through reading and podcasts, my body through health and fitness and my soul through my faith- worship, Bible reading, devotionals and prayer. Find calm in the chaos. 

#mistydawn3431

I grew up with a single Momma. She struggled every day but never gave up. She loved me unconditionally. She passed away when I was 33 from lung cancer.. My childhood was tough. We were very poor. We moved a lot. There were times our utilities were turned off. My Momma would pray & she always said God will make a way, & he always did. I never realized how much we didn’t have. 
At 12, I met the neighbor boy. He was my ’boyfriend’but we weren’t dating until 15. I asked my Momma for birth control. She declined my request, assuming I would remain abstinent. There was no sexual education discussed, & I had no clue. I became pregnant at 15. I worked hard, finished school, went to cosmetology school. I married my daughter’s Father at 19, divorced at 21. 
After a yr of being single, I started dating my husband now. We met in the 4th grade. He had a 1yr old, & mine was 5. We blended our family, although we never say step. We married & had a daughter at 23. We bought our home, & later welcomed another daughter at 26. 15 years later, we’re still going strong. 
I prayed and wrote on January 1st, 2nd & 3rd first thing in the morning. I thanked the Lord & asked him to use me big this year for HIS will. On January 3rd, I received a message asking for a comment on my viral video posted 1/2/24 about becoming a grandmother, from the New York Post. I saw this message too late, the deadline was 12pm. I thought the article wasn’t going to be written. At 7:59pm, I received a message from a representative @lifeprousa asking if they were the first to share the article with me. I was so surprised to be published in the @nypost 
God is using my story-my testimony to bring people to my Tik Tok account, where I share my truth, comedy, tutorials, products I love, my devotionals and my bible giveaways. So many people were kind &
“Your character always speaks for itself.
So if it’s only one person accusing you of being someone you’re not out of the many who truly know you, they are merely projecting who they are.
Don’t take it to heart. Just keep being you and walk on. It isn’t worth being the collateral damage in someone else’s war they continously fight with themselves.”
-Kayil York

Invisalign day one, tray one 

I went in, Heidi seated me. She chatted with Kelly about Janet. 

She put the cheek retractors and a tongue suction in. That was weird! She applied prophy polish. Sent me to a sink to brush with toothbrushes that had invisible toothpaste in the bristles. I thoroughly enjoyed that! 

Then she etched, bonded and my teeth. She used a template aligned to put composite where brackets would be in braces. Put that on my teeth & cured for about 3 seconds each. 

Removed the retractors, suction and sat me up. I asked when they’d do the inter-proximal reduction.

Doctor came over. He did IPR on one tooth. One. But thank the Lort! #21 was Dinosaur flossed and the contact was so tight! It broke, his hand slid and cut my lips. He said that’s embarrassing in front of a dental office employee. (It happens) His fingers were buried into my lower left anterior area. After all that finally worked,  he put my trays in. They fit perfect. He said nice job on the bonding Heidi. 

I was given a magnetic case, & 25 of 29 trays. I go back in 14 weeks. 

Took em out, ate and two bumps fell off. I called and they said it’s fine, unless I lose more. 

My teeth feel like concrete is lathered all over them and it’s not smooth. Idk how I’ll know when they’re clean. I’ll just brush forever I guess. I prefer the trays on to not feel that. 

Nobody says they have a plastic taste or bumps between to line up your new bite. I had no idea about that. 

Tray 25 looks pretty good! So I’m excited for June 28th. 

I’m not in pain and talk fine. Overall a good experience so far! 🥰 #Invisalign #invisalignjourney #clearaligners #ortho #mistydawn3431
5 years ago we got this beauty 😍

5 years ago today my life changed forever. My Momma was diagnosed with #lungcancer. She lost her battle with cancer 1 year & 7 months later, on 8/17/2020. 

I prayed for God to heal her from the time I woke up, until I fell asleep. I would even stay awake with insomnia praying. My #anticipatorygrief was so bad. My worry, anxiety and fear of losing my Momma was horrible. 

The more I prayed, the worse she got. Every person gets a different amount of time in this life with their mothers, just like everyone has an entirely different relationship with them. My time with my Momma was cut short and I didn’t get to have her as long as I would have liked. I do try to remember there are people that had less time, a lot less & no closure or anticipatory grief. I cherish us living each day like it was the last together. My years with my Momma were short, but our relationship was way beyond our years. My mother was my everything. She was my best friend and my confident. I lost way more than just my Momma when she died.

They say a mother and a daughter is one of the closest relationships in the world. Losing that relationship taught me how capable I was of loving, losing, and feeling pain. She loved me & my family unconditionally, no matter what. I share that bond with each of my girls. I know that God gave me them so that I could make it without her. So that I would still have that type of relationship, and understand her love for you me.

At first I was at peace and so relieved she wasn’t in pain and suffering anymore. Then grief came in waves of depression and anger. I was mad at the world and mad at God. Eventually I worked through my emotions and realized anger was just a reaction to the amount of loss and sadness I felt. I have all of this love, that’s always been hers and no where to share it. It was her individual, special love. I also missed the reciprocal love. I missed maternal guidance. I was so consumed with why God would take her & leave my alcoholic drug addict Father that has nothing to do with me. I envied every Mother Daughter duo & dreaded every day. 

But God. Her love in life & death always pointed me to him. He did answer my prayers. She is healed.
I thought I was the only one 😅text myself too 🤣
He gets better & better with age 😍 #mistydawn3431
